Former students of Masinde Muliro University of Science and Technology want the EACC to withdraw its suspension of the institution’s Vice Chancellor, Fredrick Otieno. Speaking in Kakamega yesterday, the university’s alumni association said infighting at the institution was eroding its credibility. They expressed anger over recent negative news about the university. In November last year, the Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission recommended Otieno’s suspension over corruption allegations. Read: EACC wants Masinde Muliro VC suspended over funds misuse, abuse of office “We are calling for the EACC to recall its letter to the council recommending the suspension of the VC. We want the EACC to instead carry out independent investigations of the entire system, beginning with the Chairperson of the University Council,” the association’s chairman, Kennedy Echesa, said. Click here for the latest political news